.TH "cap_bprm_creds_from_file" 9 "cap_bprm_creds_from_file" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cap_bprm_creds_from_file \- Set up the proposed credentials for execve().
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cap_bprm_creds_from_file
.BI "(struct linux_binprm *bprm "  ","
.BI "struct file *file "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bprm" 12
The execution parameters, including the proposed creds
.IP "file" 12
The file to pull the credentials from
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set up the proposed credentials for a new execution context being
constructed by \fBexecve\fP.  The proposed creds in \fIbprm->cred\fP is altered,
which won't take effect immediately.  Returns 0 if successful, -ve on error.
